<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 2:17AM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTHWESTERN WARD,
NORTHWESTERN RENVILLE AND NORTHEASTERN BURKE COUNTIES THROUGH 245 AM
CDT...
At 217 AM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 10 miles northeast
of Bowbells, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Ward,
northwestern Renville and northeastern Burke Counties, including the
following locations... Coteau and Northgate.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
